cat's eye
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a shellfish (<i>Turbo</i> spp.) which closes the entry to its shell with a horny valve (`operculum') resembling a cat's eye in shape and colour;
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:also ataata
Pronunciation:
Notes:
Citations
Date: 0/0/1947
Source: Native Animals of NZ
Author: POWELL
Vol / Page: 26
Edition:
Quote: CAT'S EYE (<i>Lunella smaragda</i>). Best known of all our shells of intertidal rocks. ... The circular greenish operculum, the cat's eye, is its most conspicuous feature. The Maori name is Ataata.
