Edition:
Quote: They had no gun but they cooked limpets and bu-bus (the catseye shell) and a few pauas to keep them going. <i>Ibid.</i> 184 [Horse Shoe Bay] is a good beach on which to find the big strong shells, the ostrich-foot, a big whelk, and the southern volute, or dog shell, the lunella or catseye shell, and the rare modelia, also with a catseye to close its door.
